$interpreted: Kittyeyes: Alright, alright; you can keep sleeping. I'll leave the food here. If you're hungry, you can help yourself.
Roger: Kittyeyes, how long are you going to let that wolf stay here?
Kittyeyes: Roger, he just recovered from his injuries. Can't you let him stay here a while longer?
Roger: I can already tell what you're thinking, and my answer is no. I will not allow you to keep it as a pet!
Kittyeyes: WHY!
Roger: We don't have the resources to waste on useless junk. Other folks have to work their butts off with me in order to earn a living.
Roger: No reason only "it" can live and eat for free.
Kittyeyes: Are you serious? You're making a fuss over a tiny wolf cub?
Kittyeyes: Whatever, can't talk sense into Roger anyway. You, leave, now!
Roger: Hey, wait a minute. HEY!
Wolf Cub: Woo...
Roger: Didn't expect Kittyeyes to be so mad...better coax her a bit later, or else days are gonna be tough from now on.
Roger: I got it; let's have a barbeque party tonight!
Roger: ...What the heck, you scared away all the meat! I'll teach you a harsh lesson!
Roger: Hey, what are you doing here, back off!
Wolf Cub: Grrrrrrr~~
Roger: Hoho~ so you wanna prove that you have the ability to stay? Very well, show me what you are capable of.
Roger: Is that the best you got?
Wolf Cub: Arooo...
Roger: ...But you did put up a pretty good fight. Some proper training and you'll be good enough to help us out.
Wolf Cub: Woo!?
Roger: That means that you can stay with us. Understand?
Roger: Stop it. I said stop it; I'm not Kittyeyes.
Roger: The ones you like are no good. I won't allow it!
Kittyeyes: The ones like said are even more terrible than mine!
Kittyeyes: Ah, nice timing. We are just discussing your name.
Kittyeyes: Do you prefer "Marie Rose", "Lucky Chloe" or "Snow White"?
Roger: It's not a female wolf. Everyone's gonna laugh at him with names like that.
Roger: Check out the names I came up with: "Death Storm", "Darkness Harbinger", "Nightmare Soul";
Roger: Pretty cool, right!
Kittyeyes: Roger, your names suck!
Roger: Better than yours.
Roger: Come on, my names are better, right?
Kittyeyes: No, my names are better, right? Quick, pick one!
Jeff: Koll, why do you look so terrified?
Wolf Cub: Arooooo~
Roger: Jeff, what did you just call him?
Jeff: Koll. I've been calling him like this for a few days now. It's easy to remember.
Koll: Arooooo~
Kittyeyes: Looks like...he likes this name more than the others?
Roger: Is that so? But my names are seriously awesome...
Kittyeyes: Okay, a conclusion has been reached. Starting today, your name will be Koll!
Koll: Arooooo~
